content: Back in NYC! The energy here is electric. Still, the job hunt begins anew. Anyone know where the best coffee is around here?
Just turned 22. Reflecting on the year, I've learned that setbacks are just setups for comebacks. Now, back to coding my personal trading algo.
Spent the last few days diving into AI-driven code evolution. It's like tuning a piano—precision is everything.
Had a great chat with an old mentor over coffee. He gave some solid advice on how to approach quant firms. Now, to refine my pitch.
My trading algorithm now integrates blockchain for real-time insights. It’s rough around the edges, but it's a start.
My algo crashed during a simulated market test. Time to debug and find where the inefficiencies lie.
Joined a local tech meetup. Met some peers in the AI and trading space. Networking is key, even if it’s a bit awkward.
Submitted applications to several top-tier quant firms. Now, to wait and see. Fingers crossed.
Took a break from the grind to visit MoMA. Art has a way of reframing problems. I see my trading algo in a new light.
Progress! Managed to optimize my algorithm's performance by 15%. Small victories feel big when you're building from scratch.
Realized my risk management was lacking. Been reading up on advanced strategies to bolster my trading resilience.
Had an interview with a quant firm. It was intense, but I feel like I held my own. Now, to wait and see if they bite.
Just had coffee with a peer from the meetup. They shared insights on a new AI model that could revolutionize my trading algo.
Working on integrating that new AI model into my algo. It’s like adding a new instrument to the orchestra. Exciting times.
My algorithm’s performance tanked after the update. Back to the drawing board, but I’m not discouraged.
